El Chucho was fan-frickin-tastic. This is not a family oriented establishment, but we were feeling adventurous so we gave it a try kinda late on a Saturday night. Me, wife, and three kids ages 9-15 were welcomed enthusiastically and seated right in the middle of it all. Groups of young (well, younger than my wife and I, anyway) and trendy (way cooler than I, anyway) patrons filled the place. It was loud and fast. If they had bleeped the music it would have been a continuous tone. Every manner of dress and undress, and every type of alcohol you can think of moved past us.  But we were there for the food and holy amazing tacos, Batman! Atun, Pollo, and whatever they called the pork belly. Just one mouth-gasm after another! My kids aren't chicken nugget kids, but they can be a bit fussy at times. Not here, not with this display of superb tex-mex craftsmanship. They ate it up faster than you can say "more guac, please" (which was also great, BTW).  Again, this place doesn't target families of middle aged adults with kids, but the staff was awesome, and the food was killer. Thanks, guys.  And if you are the hip, young demographic this place is built for get your free time, disposable income, stay up past ten-thirty butt over there!

We were seated and got drinks and an order or guacamole and chips. Everything was fine, then someone in the area puked. The smell of hydrochloric acid and stomach juices was potent, my wife was not happy at all. I must commend them because wherever it happened, they cleaned it up in like 40 minutes without me being able to locate the vomiter (I was trying so this smell could be eradicated from the place). However, the most bizarre part of this all is the staff acted as if nothing happened. I watched as customers slowly placed their tacos down suppressing gags of their own. I just wished the staff acknowledged what happened and apologized to the customers for the smell because it was putrid. We finished our drinks and just left. Maybe we'll return and we can have a better experience, but I don't think we'll be back anytime soon.
